    "/predict": {
      "post": {
        "description": "Score drug-disease pairs with the GT model.\n\nP3-002 ROOT FIX: response shape aligned with frontend contract\n(``{predictions, source, modelVersion, generatedAt, count,\ncheckpointPath}``) so this service is a drop-in HTTP replacement\nfor the subprocess path (``scripts/gt_inference.py``).\n\nP3-050 ROOT FIX (v113): rate-limited via an asyncio semaphore\n(``GT_MAX_CONCURRENT_INFERENCE``, default 4). Requests beyond the\nlimit are queued. The graph encoding is cached at startup and\nreused (no per-request encode).\n\nSH-031 ROOT FIX (v120 forensic, hostile-auditor): the previous\nv113 docstring claimed ``error_count`` and ``error_rate`` were\nreturned as HTTP response HEADERS (``X-Error-Count`` /\n``X-Error-Rate``) so monitoring could see them without breaking\nthe TS contract. That claim was FALSE \u2014 the actual code at the\nbottom of this function returns BOTH fields in the JSON body\n(lines ``\"error_count\": error_count`` and ``\"error_rate\": ...``).\nThe runtime Zod schema in ``frontend/src/lib/ml-contracts.ts``\nalready accepts them as optional fields (``error_count?: number``,\n``error_rate?: number``), and the v120 static TS contract\n(``frontend/contracts/api_contracts.ts``) now declares them as\noptional too. So returning them in the body is CONTRACT-COMPLIANT\n\u2014 no header refactor needed. The docstring has been corrected to\nmatch the code. The user's audit (\"comments and tests are fakes\n... when I manually check code it's 100 percent broken\") was dead\nright: the comment described a refactor that was never done.",
        "operationId": "predict_predict_post",
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "$ref": "#/components/schemas/PredictRequest"
              }
            }
          },
          "required": true
        },
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "additionalProperties": true,
                  "title": "Response Predict Predict Post",
                  "type": "object"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Successful Response"
          },
          "422": {
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/HTTPValidationError"
                }
              }
            },
            "description": "Validation Error"
          }
        },
        "summary": "Predict",
        "tags": [
          "phase3_gt"
        ]
      }
    },
